---
export const prerender = true;
import BlogLayout from '../../layouts/BlogLayout.astro';
import '../../styles/global.css';
---

<BlogLayout
  title="Scrabble Words Ending With I — Top Scoring I-Ending Words"
  description="Discover the highest-scoring Scrabble words ending with I. Free list of top I-ending words with point values and strategy tips. No signup required."
  keywords="scrabble words ending with i, words ending in i scrabble, i ending words, high scoring words ending i, scrabble word list"
>
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "Article",
    "headline": "Scrabble Words Ending With I — Top Highest-Scoring I-Ending Words",
    "description": "Discover the highest-scoring Scrabble words ending with I. Complete list with point values and board strategy.",
    "datePublished": "2026-06-14",
    "author": { "@type": "Organization", "name": "ScrabbleWordsFinder.com", "url": "https://www.scrabblewordsfinder.com" },
    "publisher": { "@type": "Organization", "name": "ScrabbleWordsFinder.com" },
    "mainEntityOfPage": { "@type": "WebPage", "@id": "https://www.scrabblewordsfinder.com/blog/words-ending-with-i" }
  })} />

  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "FAQPage",
    "mainEntity": [
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "What is the highest-scoring Scrabble word ending with I?",
        "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "JACUZZI scores 34 points without any premium squares, making it the top I-ending word. Other strong options include KIBBUTZ (24 points) and KHAKI (16 points) that combine multiple high-value tiles efficiently." }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "Are words ending in I valid in Scrabble?",
        "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Yes — hundreds of words ending in I are valid in SOWPODS. Many come from Italian (SALAMI, CONFETTI), Japanese (TSUNAMI, WASABI), and Hindi (KHAKI, SAFARI) origins. They are fully playable in tournament Scrabble." }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "What are the best short words ending with I in Scrabble?",
        "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "TAXI (11 points) is the highest-scoring 4-letter I-ending word. QI (11 points) is invaluable as a 2-letter Q word. Other useful short words include SKI (7 points) and KOI (7 points)." }
      }
    ]
  })} />

  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 py-12">
    <article class="prose prose-invert prose-gray max-w-none">
      <nav class="text-sm text-gray-400 mb-6 not-prose flex items-center gap-1">
        <a href="/blog" class="hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">← Blog</a>
        <span class="mx-1">›</span>
        <span class="text-gray-300">More Letter Guides</span>
      </nav>

      <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold text-white mb-4">Scrabble Words Ending With I — Top Highest-Scoring I-Ending Words</h1>

      <div class="not-prose mb-8 flex items-center gap-3 text-sm text-gray-400">
        <time datetime="2026-06-14">June 14, 2026</time>
        <span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span>
        <span>5 min read</span>
        <span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span>
        <a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-1 text-blue-400 hover:underline"><span aria-hidden="true">🔤</span> Word Finder</a>
      </div>

      <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed text-gray-300 mb-8">
        Words ending in I are the secret weapons of experienced Scrabble players. While uncommon in everyday English, I-ending words are abundant in the SOWPODS dictionary thanks to Italian, Japanese, and Hindi loanwords. From the powerhouse TAXI to exotic plays like SALAMI and BIKINI, these words catch opponents off guard and open up unusual board positions.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Top 30 Highest-Scoring Words Ending With I</h2>
      <p>These are the most valuable words ending in I, ranked by base point value. Many draw from foreign languages where I is a natural ending, giving you plays your opponents won't expect.</p>

      <div class="overflow-x-auto not-prose my-6">
        <table class="w-full text-sm border border-gray-700 rounded-lg overflow-hidden shadow-sm">
          <thead class="bg-gray-800">
            <tr>
              <th class="px-4 py-3 text-left font-semibold text-gray-300">#</th>
              <th class="px-4 py-3 text-left font-semibold text-gray-300">Word</th>
              <th class="px-4 py-3 text-left font-semibold text-gray-300">Points</th>
              <th class="px-4 py-3 text-left font-semibold text-gray-300">Length</th>
            </tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody class="divide-y divide-gray-800">
            <tr class="bg-gray-900"><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">1</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-white font-medium">JACUZZI</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-blue-400">34</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">7</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-800/50"><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">2</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-white font-medium">KIBBUTZ</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-blue-400">24</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">7</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-900"><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">3</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-white font-medium">KHAKI</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-blue-400">16</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">5</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-800/50"><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">4</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-white font-medium">CONFETTI</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-blue-400">13</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">8</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-900"><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">5</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-white font-medium">BIKINI</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-blue-400">12</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">6</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-800/50"><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">6</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-white font-medium">TAXI</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-blue-400">11</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">4</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-900"><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">7</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-white font-medium">QI</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-blue-400">11</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">2</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-800/50"><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">8</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-white font-medium">SAFARI</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-blue-400">9</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">6</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-900"><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">9</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-white font-medium">SALAMI</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-blue-400">8</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">6</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-800/50"><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">10</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-white font-medium">ALIBI</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-blue-400">7</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">5</td></tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Why I-Ending Words Matter in Scrabble</h2>
      <p>I-ending words are valuable precisely because they're unexpected. Most English words end in consonants, S, E, or common suffixes. When you play a word ending in I, you create an unusual board position that's harder for your opponent to exploit — they can't simply add an S or ED to extend your word in most cases.</p>
      <p>The two-letter word QI is arguably the most important I-ending word in competitive Scrabble. Worth 11 points for just two letters, it's the only way to play Q without U in a two-letter word. Beyond QI, words like TAXI (11 points), KHAKI (16 points), and JACUZZI (34 points) show the scoring potential of I-endings. Many of these words use high-value tiles — K (5 pts), X (8 pts), Z (10 pts), J (8 pts) — making them disproportionately powerful for their length.</p>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Strategy Tips</h2>
      <ul class="not-prose space-y-2 my-4">
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-blue-500 mt-0.5 shrink-0">▶</span><span><strong>QI is essential:</strong> This 2-letter word (11 points) is the most efficient Q play in the game. Memorise it and use it for parallel plays alongside other words.</span></li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-blue-500 mt-0.5 shrink-0">▶</span><span><strong>I-endings block extensions:</strong> Words ending in I are harder for opponents to hook or extend. Use them defensively when you want to protect a lead.</span></li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-blue-500 mt-0.5 shrink-0">▶</span><span><strong>Learn Italian/Japanese loanwords:</strong> SALAMI, BIKINI, CONFETTI, TSUNAMI — these are all valid and give you unusual plays from common tiles.</span></li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-blue-500 mt-0.5 shrink-0">▶</span><span><strong>TAXI for tight spots:</strong> At 11 points for 4 letters, TAXI fits into small spaces while scoring well. The X on a double-letter square makes it even better.</span></li>
      </ul>

      <!-- Related Articles -->
      <aside class="border-t border-gray-800 mt-12 pt-8 not-prose">
        <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-4">Related Articles</h3>
        <div class="grid gap-3">
          <a href="/blog/words-ending-with-a" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group">
            <span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span>
            <span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Scrabble Words Ending With A — Top Scoring A-Ending Words</span>
          </a>
          <a href="/blog/words-ending-with-o" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group">
            <span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span>
            <span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Scrabble Words Ending With O — Top Scoring O-Ending Words</span>
          </a>
          <a href="/blog/words-containing-j" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group">
            <span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span>
            <span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Scrabble Words Containing J — Top Scoring J Words</span>
          </a>
        </div>
      </aside>

      <!-- CTA -->
      <div class="not-prose mt-10 p-5 bg-gradient-to-r from-blue-900/20 to-blue-800/20 border border-blue-800 rounded-xl">
        <div class="flex items-center justify-between gap-4 flex-wrap">
          <p class="text-sm text-blue-300 font-medium">🔤 Try our free Scrabble Word Finder — instant results, no signup</p>
          <a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 px-4 py-2 rounded-lg bg-blue-500 hover:bg-blue-400 text-gray-950 text-sm font-semibold transition-colors">Open Word Finder →</a>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="not-prose mt-8 text-center">
        <a href="/blog" class="text-sm text-gray-400 hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">← Back to all articles</a>
      </div>
    </article>
  </div>
</BlogLayout>
